{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775850546623,"sessionID":"ses_2870f54e9ffeZYvuDZque7APgc","part":{"id":"prt_d78f0da9e001JMjHDlHaVs2t4H","messageID":"msg_d78f0c0e1001bSz0Cg2Sk2RjeW","sessionID":"ses_2870f54e9ffeZYvuDZque7APgc","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-f53f4863033a4e5dad660fe98275b112","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-009/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-009/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-009 — Router HTTP 反向代理核心\n2: \n3: **Module:** `pkg/router`  \n4: **Language:** Go  \n5: **Size:** M\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Overview\n10: \n11: Define the HTTP reverse proxy core for the AgentCube Router component. This provides session-aware routing that resolves session IDs from request headers, creates sandboxes via Workload Manager, forwards HTTP requests to sandbox pod endpoints using `httputil.ReverseProxy`, generates RS256-signed JWT tokens, updates session activity timestamps, and limits concurrent requests via semaphore middleware.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: Server type definition\n18: \n19: The system SHALL define `Server` as an HTTP server with Gin engine for reverse proxy routing.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Server struct definition\n22: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/server.go`\n23: - **WHEN** reading the `Server` struct\n24: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n25:   - `config *Config` for server configuration\n26:   - `engine *gin.Engine` for Gin HTTP framework\n27:   - `httpServer *http.Server` for underlying HTTP server\n28:   - `sessionManager SessionManager` for session resolution\n29:   - `store Store` for session state persistence\n30:   - `jwtManager JWTManager` for JWT token generation\n31:   - `transport *http.Transport` for HTTP transport sharing\n32:   - `logger Logger` for structured logging\n33: \n34: #### Scenario: Config struct definition\n35: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/config.go`\n36: - **WHEN** reading the `Config` struct\n37: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n38:   - `Port int` for listening port (default 8080)\n39:   - `EnableTLS bool` for TLS enablement\n40:   - `TLSCert string` for TLS certificate file path\n41:   - `TLSKey string` for TLS private key file path\n42:   - `MaxConcurrentRequests int` for concurrency limit\n43:   - `Debug bool` for debug mode\n44: \n45: #### Scenario: NewServer constructor\n46: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/server.go`\n47: - **WHEN** calling `NewServer(config *Config, sessionManager SessionManager, store Store, jwtManager JWTManager, logger Logger)`\n48: - **THEN** it SHALL return `*Server` with:\n49:   - `engine` initialized with `gin.New()`\n50:   - `gin.SetMode(gin.ReleaseMode)` if `config.Debug == false`\n51:   - `gin.SetMode(gin.DebugMode)` if `config.Debug == true`\n52:   - `transport` initialized with shared HTTP transport\n53:   - `httpServer` initialized with h2c configuration\n54: \n55: #### Scenario: DefaultConfig\n56: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/config.go`\n57: - **WHEN** calling `DefaultConfig()`\n58: - **THEN** it SHALL return `*Config` with:\n59:   - `Port` = `8080`\n60:   - `EnableTLS` = `false`\n61:   - `MaxConcurrentRequests` = `1000`\n62: \n63: ---\n64: \n65: ### Requirement: Server lifecycle\n66: \n67: The system SHALL provide Start/Stop lifecycle methods with graceful shutdown.\n68: \n69: #### Scenario: Start without TLS\n70: - **GIVEN** a `Server` with `config.EnableTLS == false`\n71: - **WHEN** calling `server.Start(ctx)`\n72: - **THEN** `httpServer.ListenAndServe()` SHALL be called\n73: - AND h2c server SHALL handle HTTP/2 without TLS\n74: \n75: #### Scenario: Start with TLS\n76: - **GIVEN** a `Server` with `config.EnableTLS == true`\n77: - **WHEN** calling `server.Start(ctx)`\n78: - **THEN** `httpServer.ListenAndServeTLS(config.TLSCert, config.TLSKey)` SHALL be called\n79: - AND error SHALL be returned if cert/key files are missing\n80: \n81: #### Scenario: Graceful shutdown\n82: - **GIVEN** a running `Server`\n83: - **WHEN** context is cancelled\n84: - **THEN** `httpServer.Shutdown(shutdownCtx)` SHALL be called\n85: - AND shutdown deadline SHALL be `10s`\n86: - AND server SHALL stop accepting new connections\n87: - AND existing connections SHALL complete\n88: \n89: #### Scenario: Server timeouts\n90: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/server.go`\n91: - **WHEN** initializing `httpServer`\n92: - **THEN** timeouts SHALL be configured:\n93:   - `ReadTimeout` = `30s`\n94:   - `IdleTimeout` = `90s`\n95: \n96: ---\n97: \n98: ### Requirement: Route registration\n99: \n100: The system SHALL register routes for health endpoints and invocation paths.\n101: \n102: #### Scenario: Health routes\n103: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/server.go`\n104: - **WHEN** registering routes\n105: - **THEN** `/health/live` SHALL be registered with `handleHealthLive`\n106: - AND `/health/ready` SHALL be registered with `handleHealthReady`\n107: \n108: #### Scenario: Invocation routes\n109: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/server.go`\n110: - **WHEN** registering routes\n111: - **THEN** `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path` SHALL be registered\n112: - AND `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path` SHALL be registered\n113: - AND both `GET` and `POST` methods SHALL be supported\n114: \n115: #### Scenario: Middleware chain\n116: - **GIVEN** route registration\n117: - **WHEN** applying middleware\n118: - **THEN** `concurrencyLimitMiddleware` SHALL be applied globally\n119: - AND `loggingMiddleware` SHALL be applied for request logging\n120: - AND `recoveryMiddleware` SHALL be applied for panic recovery\n121: \n122: ---\n123: \n124: ### Requirement: SessionManager interface\n125: \n126: The system SHALL define `SessionManager` interface for session resolution and sandbox creation.\n127: \n128: #### Scenario: SessionManager interface definition\n129: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n130: - **WHEN** reading the `SessionManager` interface\n131: - **THEN** interface SHALL include:\n132:   - `GetSandboxBySession(ctx context.Context, sessionID, namespace, name, kind string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n133: \n134: #### Scenario: manager struct definition\n135: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n136: - **WHEN** reading the `manager` struct\n137: - **THEN** struct SHALL contain:\n138:   - `storeClient Store` for session lookup\n139:   - `workloadMgrAddr string` for Workload Manager URL\n140:   - `httpClient *http.Client` for sandbox creation requests\n141:   - `logger Logger` for structured logging\n142: \n143: #### Scenario: NewSessionManager constructor\n144: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n145: - **WHEN** calling `NewSessionManager(store Store, logger Logger)`\n146: - **THEN** it SHALL return `*manager` with:\n147:   - `workloadMgrAddr` from `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` environment variable\n148:   - startup SHALL fail if `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` is not set\n149:   - `httpClient` with `Timeout=2m`, `MaxIdleConnsPerHost=100`\n150: \n151: #### Scenario: HTTP client configuration\n152: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n153: - **WHEN** initializing `httpClient`\n154: - **THEN** HTTP2 SHALL be configured with:\n155:   - `ReadIdleTimeout` = `30s`\n156:   - `PingTimeout` = `15s`\n157: \n158: ---\n159: \n160: ### Requirement: Session resolution\n161: \n162: The system SHALL resolve sessions by ID and create new sandboxes when missing.\n163: \n164: #### Scenario: GetSandboxBySession with existing session\n165: - **GIVEN** a session ID that exists in store\n166: - **WHEN** calling `GetSandboxBySession(ctx, sessionID, namespace, name, kind)`\n167: - **THEN** `store.GetSession(ctx, sessionID)` SHALL be called\n168: - AND `*SandboxInfo` SHALL be returned if found\n169: \n170: #### Scenario: GetSandboxBySession creates new sandbox\n171: - **GIVEN** a session ID that does NOT exist in store\n172: - **WHEN** calling `GetSandboxBySession(ctx, sessionID, namespace, name, kind)`\n173: - **THEN** `createSandbox(ctx, namespace, name, kind)` SHALL be called\n174: - AND POST request SHALL be sent to Workload Manager\n175: \n176: #### Scenario: createSandbox POST request\n177: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n178: - **WHEN** calling `createSandbox(ctx, namespace, name, kind)`\n179: - **THEN** POST SHALL be sent to:\n180:   - `/v1/agent-runtime` for `AgentRuntimeKind`\n181:   - `/v1/code-interpreter` for `CodeInterpreterKind`\n182: - AND request body SHALL be `CreateSandboxRequest`\n183: \n184: #### Scenario: createSandbox with K8s SA token\n185: - **GIVEN** in-cluster deployment\n186: - **WHEN** sending POST to Workload Manager\n187: - **THEN** `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` SHALL be read\n188: - AND token SHALL be set as `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header\n189: \n190: #### Scenario: createSandbox namespace\n191: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n192: - **WHEN** creating sandbox\n193: - **THEN** `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` environment variable SHALL be read for target namespace\n194: - AND default namespace SHALL be `\"default\"` if not set\n195: \n196: ---\n197: \n198: ### Requirement: Reverse proxy implementation\n199: \n200: The system SHALL implement reverse proxy with custom Director and error handling.\n201: \n202: #### Scenario: ReverseProxy struct definition\n203: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/reverse_proxy.go`\n204: - **WHEN** reading the implementation\n205: - **THEN** `httputil.NewSingleHostReverseProxy` SHALL be used as base\n206: - AND custom `Director` function SHALL be set\n207: - AND custom `ModifyResponse` function SHALL be set\n208: - AND custom `ErrorHandler` function SHALL be set\n209: \n210: #### Scenario: Director path normalization\n211: - **GIVEN** a request with path `/api/run`\n212: - **WHEN** Director processes the request\n213: - **THEN** leading slash SHALL be prefixed if missing: `//api/run` → `/api/run`\n214: - AND path SHALL match entry point from `SandboxInfo.EntryPoints`\n215: \n216: #### Scenario: Director forwarding headers\n217: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/reverse_proxy.go`\n218: - **WHEN** Director processes request\n219: - **THEN** `req.Host` SHALL be set to target host\n220: - AND `X-Forwarded-For` SHALL be set with client IP\n221: - AND `X-Real-IP` SHALL be set with client IP\n222: \n223: #### Scenario: Director JWT injection\n224: - **GIVEN** a proxied request\n225: - **WHEN** Director processes request\n226: - **THEN** JWT token SHALL be generated by `jwtManager`\n227: - AND `Authorization: Bearer <jwt>` SHALL be added to request headers\n228: \n229: #### Scenario: ModifyResponse session header injection\n230: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/reverse_proxy.go`\n231: - **WHEN** ModifyResponse processes response\n232: - **THEN** `x-agentcube-session-id` header SHALL be added to response\n233: - AND value SHALL be the resolved session ID\n234: \n235: #### Scenario: ErrorHandler connection refused\n236: - **GIVEN** proxy error with connection refused\n237: - **WHEN** ErrorHandler processes error\n238: - **THEN** HTTP `502` SHALL be returned\n239: - AND error code SHALL be `sandbox unreachable`\n240: \n241: #### Scenario: ErrorHandler timeout\n242: - **GIVEN** proxy error with timeout\n243: - **WHEN** ErrorHandler processes error\n244: - **THEN** HTTP `504` SHALL be returned\n245: - AND error code SHALL be `sandbox timeout`\n246: \n247: #### Scenario: Entry point matching\n248: - **GIVEN** `SandboxInfo.EntryPoints` with multiple entry points\n249: - **WHEN** selecting entry point\n250: - **THEN** first entry point with matching path prefix SHALL be used\n251: - AND `Endpoint` SHALL be the proxy target URL\n252: \n253: ---\n254: \n255: ### Requirement: JWT Manager\n256: \n257: The system SHALL implement JWT token generation with RSA signing and K8s Secret persistence.\n258: \n259: #### Scenario: JWTManager interface definition\n260: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n261: - **WHEN** reading the `JWTManager` interface\n262: - **THEN** interface SHALL include:\n263:   - `GenerateToken(ctx context.Context, kind, name, namespace string) (string, error)`\n264:   - `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret(ctx context.Context) error`\n265: \n266: #### Scenario: jwtManager struct definition\n267: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n268: - **WHEN** reading the `jwtManager` struct\n269: - **THEN** struct SHALL contain:\n270:   - `privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey` for RSA private key\n271:   - `publicKey *rsa.PublicKey` for RSA public key\n272:   - `kubeClient kubernetes.Interface` for K8s Secret operations\n273:   - `namespace string` for Secret namespace\n274:   - `logger Logger` for structured logging\n275: \n276: #### Scenario: RSA key generation\n277: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n278: - **WHEN** generating RSA key\n279: - **THEN** `rsa.GenerateKey(rand.Reader, 2048)` SHALL be called\n280: - AND key size SHALL be `2048` bits (constant `rsaKeySize`)\n281: - AND private key SHALL be PKCS1 encoded\n282: - AND public key SHALL be PKIX encoded\n283: \n284: #### Scenario: GenerateToken\n285: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n286: - **WHEN** calling `GenerateToken(ctx, kind, name, namespace)`\n287: - **THEN** JWT SHALL be created with claims:\n288:   - `exp` = `now + 5m` (constant `jwtExpiration`)\n289:   - `iat` = `now`\n290:   - `iss` = `\"agentcube-router\"`\n291:   - `kind` = kind parameter\n292:   - `name` = name parameter\n293:   - `namespace` = namespace parameter\n294: - AND JWT SHALL be signed with RS256 algorithm\n295: \n296: #### Scenario: TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret create\n297: - **GIVEN** no existing Secret `picod-router-identity`\n298: - **WHEN** calling `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret(ctx)`\n299: - **THEN** K8s Secret SHALL be created with:\n300:   - `name` = `IdentitySecretName` (`\"picod-router-identity\"`)\n301:   - `data[\"private-key\"]` = PKCS1 encoded private key\n302:   - `data[\"public-key\"]` = PKIX encoded public key\n303: \n304: #### Scenario: TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret load\n305: - **GIVEN** existing Secret `picod-router-identity`\n306: - **WHEN** calling `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret(ctx)`\n307: - **THEN** Secret SHALL be loaded via `kubeClient.CoreV1().Secrets(namespace).Get`\n308: - AND keys SHALL be decoded from Secret data\n309: - AND `privateKey` and `publicKey` SHALL be set from loaded data\n310: \n311: #### Scenario: TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret AlreadyExists\n312: - **GIVEN** multiple router replicas starting simultaneously\n313: - **WHEN** Secret creation returns `AlreadyExists` error\n314: - **THEN** existing Secret SHALL be loaded instead\n315: - AND no error SHALL be returned\n316: \n317: ---\n318: \n319: ### Requirement: Middleware concurrency limit\n320: \n321: The system SHALL limit concurrent requests using semaphore middleware.\n322: \n323: #### Scenario: concurrencyLimitMiddleware\n324: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/middleware.go`\n325: - **WHEN** reading middleware implementation\n326: - **THEN** buffered channel SHALL be used as semaphore\n327: - AND channel capacity SHALL be `MaxConcurrentRequests`\n328: - AND default capacity SHALL be `1000` when `MaxConcurrentRequests <= 0`\n329: \n330: #### Scenario: Request acquires semaphore\n331: - **GIVEN** middleware with capacity 1000\n332: - **WHEN** request enters middleware\n333: - **THEN** `semaphore <- struct{}{}` SHALL acquire slot\n334: - AND request SHALL proceed if slot available\n335: \n336: #### Scenario: Semaphore full returns 429\n337: - **GIVEN** middleware with all slots occupied\n338: - **WHEN** new request enters middleware\n339: - **THEN** `select` with `default` case SHALL trigger\n340: - AND HTTP `429` SHALL be returned\n341: - AND response body SHALL have `SERVER_OVERLOADED` code\n342: \n343: #### Scenario: Request releases semaphore\n344: - **GIVEN** request completing processing\n345: - **WHEN** middleware exits\n346: - **THEN** `<-semaphore` SHALL release slot\n347: - AND deferred release SHALL guarantee cleanup\n348: \n349: ---\n350: \n351: ### Requirement: Health handlers\n352: \n353: The system SHALL implement health endpoints for Kubernetes probes.\n354: \n355: #### Scenario: handleHealthLive\n356: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/handlers.go`\n357: - **WHEN** calling `/health/live`\n358: - **THEN** HTTP `200` SHALL be returned\n359: - AND body SHALL be `{\"status\":\"alive\"}`\n360: \n361: #### Scenario: handleHealthReady sessionManager nil\n362: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/handlers.go`\n363: - **WHEN** calling `/health/ready` with `sessionManager == nil`\n364: - **THEN** HTTP `503` SHALL be returned\n365: - AND body SHALL indicate service unavailable\n366: \n367: #### Scenario: handleHealthReady sessionManager set\n368: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/handlers.go`\n369: - **WHEN** calling `/health/ready` with valid `sessionManager`\n370: - **THEN** HTTP `200` SHALL be returned\n371: - AND body SHALL be `{\"status\":\"ready\"}`\n372: \n373: ---\n374: \n375: ### Requirement: Invocation handler\n376: \n377: The system SHALL implement invocation handler for proxying requests to sandboxes.\n378: \n379: #### Scenario: handleInvoke extracts session ID\n380: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/handlers.go`\n381: - **WHEN** processing invocation request\n382: - **THEN** `x-agentcube-session-id` header SHALL be read\n383: - AND session ID SHALL be extracted for session resolution\n384: \n385: #### Scenario: handleInvoke resolves session\n386: - **GIVEN** request with session ID header\n387: - **WHEN** processing invocation\n388: - **THEN** `sessionManager.GetSandboxBySession(ctx, sessionID, namespace, name, kind)` SHALL be called\n389: - AND `namespace`, `name`, `kind` SHALL be extracted from URL path\n390: \n391: #### Scenario: handleInvoke creates new session\n392: - **GIVEN** request without session ID header\n393: - **WHEN** processing invocation\n394: - **THEN** new session ID SHALL be generated\n395: - AND new sandbox SHALL be created via session manager\n396: \n397: #### Scenario: handleInvoke proxies request\n398: - **GIVEN** resolved `SandboxInfo`\n399: - **WHEN** processing invocation\n400: - **THEN** reverse proxy SHALL forward request to `SandboxInfo.EntryPoints[0].Endpoint`\n401: - AND request body SHALL be forwarded unchanged\n402: \n403: #### Scenario: handleInvoke updates activity\n404: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/handlers.go`\n405: - **WHEN** invocation completes\n406: - **THEN** `store.UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID)` SHALL be called\n407: - AND `LastActivity` timestamp SHALL be updated twice:\n408:   - After sandbox resolution\n409:   - After proxy completion\n410: \n411: #### Scenario: handleInvoke error mapping\n412: - **GIVEN** an error from session resolution or proxy\n413: - **WHEN** returning response\n414: - **THEN** error type SHALL map to HTTP code:\n415:   - `SessionNotFoundError` → `404`\n416:   - `SandboxUnreachableError` → `502`\n417:   - `TimeoutError` → `504`\n418:   - `JWTSigningFailedError` → `500`\n419: \n420: ---\n421: \n422: ### Requirement: Error types\n423: \n424: The system SHALL define custom error types for categorizing failures.\n425: \n426: #### Scenario: SessionNotFoundError\n427: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/errors.go`\n428: - **WHEN** reading error types\n429: - **THEN** `SessionNotFoundError` SHALL be defined\n430: - AND error code SHALL be `SESSION_NOT_FOUND`\n431: \n432: #### Scenario: SandboxUnreachableError\n433: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/errors.go`\n434: - **WHEN** reading error types\n435: - **THEN** `SandboxUnreachableError` SHALL be defined\n436: - AND error code SHALL be `SANDBOX_UNREACHABLE`\n437: \n438: #### Scenario: TimeoutError\n439: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/errors.go`\n440: - **WHEN** reading error types\n441: - **THEN** `TimeoutError` SHALL be defined\n442: - AND error code SHALL be `SANDBOX_TIMEOUT`\n443: \n444: #### Scenario: JWTSigningFailedError\n445: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/errors.go`\n446: - **WHEN** reading error types\n447: - **THEN** `JWTSigningFailedError` SHALL be defined\n448: - AND error code SHALL be `JWT_SIGNING_FAILED`\n449: \n450: #### Scenario: ServerOverloadedError\n451: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/errors.go`\n452: - **WHEN** reading error types\n453: - **THEN** `ServerOverloadedError` SHALL be defined\n454: - AND error code SHALL be `SERVER_OVERLOADED`\n455: \n456: #### Scenario: APIStatus interface\n457: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/errors.go`\n458: - **WHEN** reading error types\n459: - **THEN** `APIStatus` interface SHALL be defined with:\n460:   - `Status() int` for HTTP status code\n461:   - `Code() string` for error code\n462:   - `Message() string` for error message\n463: \n464: ---\n465: \n466: ### Requirement: Store interface usage\n467: \n468: The system SHALL use Store interface for session state operations.\n469: \n470: #### Scenario: Store interface methods\n471: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n472: - **WHEN** using Store interface\n473: - **THEN** methods SHALL be used:\n474:   - `GetSession(ctx, sessionID) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n475:   - `CreateSession(ctx, sandboxInfo) error`\n476:   - `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID) error`\n477: \n478: ---\n479: \n480: ### Requirement: Environment variables\n481: \n482: The system SHALL read configuration from environment variables.\n483: \n484: #### Scenario: WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\n485: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n486: - **WHEN** initializing SessionManager\n487: - **THEN** `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` environment variable SHALL be required\n488: - AND startup SHALL fail if not set\n489: \n490: #### Scenario: AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE\n491: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n492: - **WHEN** determining namespace for sandbox creation\n493: - **THEN** `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` environment variable SHALL be read\n494: - AND default SHALL be `\"default\"` if not set\n495: \n496: ---\n497: \n498: ### Requirement: Constants\n499: \n500: The system SHALL define constants for configuration values.\n501: \n502: #### Scenario: rsaKeySize constant\n503: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n504: - **WHEN** reading constants\n505: - **THEN** `rsaKeySize` SHALL be `2048`\n506: \n507: #### Scenario: jwtExpiration constant\n508: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n509: - **WHEN** reading constants\n510: - **THEN** `jwtExpiration` SHALL be `5 * time.Minute`\n511: \n512: #### Scenario: IdentitySecretName constant\n513: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n514: - **WHEN** reading constants\n515: - **THEN** `IdentitySecretName` SHALL be `\"picod-router-identity\"`\n516: \n517: ---\n518: \n519: ### Requirement: Unit tests for Server\n520: \n521: The system SHALL have comprehensive unit tests for Server behavior.\n522: \n523: #### Scenario: TestNewServer\n524: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/server_test.go`\n525: - **WHEN** running tests\n526: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n527:   - Constructor returns valid instance\n528:   - Gin mode is set correctly based on Debug config\n529:   - All fields are properly initialized\n530: \n531: #### Scenario: TestServer_StartTLS\n532: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/server_test.go`\n533: - **WHEN** running tests\n534: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n535:   - TLS server starts with valid cert/key\n536:   - Error returned for missing cert/key files\n537: \n538: #### Scenario: TestServer_GracefulShutdown\n539: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/server_test.go`\n540: - **WHEN** running tests\n541: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n542:   - Server stops on context cancellation\n543:   - Shutdown deadline is 10s\n544:   - Existing requests complete before shutdown\n545: \n546: #### Scenario: TestServer_Routes\n547: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/server_test.go`\n548: - **WHEN** running tests\n549: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n550:   - Health routes are registered\n551:   - Invocation routes are registered\n552:   - Middleware chain is applied\n553: \n554: ---\n555: \n556: ### Requirement: Unit tests for SessionManager\n557: \n558: The system SHALL have comprehensive unit tests for SessionManager.\n559: \n560: #### Scenario: TestNewSessionManager\n561: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/session_manager_test.go`\n562: - **WHEN** running tests\n563: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n564:   - Constructor returns valid instance\n565:   - Fails when WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL not set\n566:   - HTTP client configured correctly\n567: \n568: #### Scenario: TestSessionManager_GetSandboxBySession_Existing\n569: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/session_manager_test.go`\n570: - **WHEN** running tests with existing session\n571: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n572:   - Store lookup is called\n573:   - SandboxInfo returned correctly\n574: \n575: #### Scenario: TestSessionManager_GetSandboxBySession_Create\n576: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/session_manager_test.go`\n577: - **WHEN** running tests with missing session\n578: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n579:   - POST request sent to Workload Manager\n580:   - Correct endpoint based on kind\n581:   - Sandbox created and stored\n582: \n583: #### Scenario: TestSessionManager_createSandbox\n584: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/session_manager_test.go`\n585: - **WHEN** running tests\n586: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n587:   - Request body is CreateSandboxRequest\n588:   - K8s SA token added when available\n589:   - Error handling for failed requests\n590: \n591: ---\n592: \n593: ### Requirement: Unit tests for ReverseProxy\n594: \n595: The system SHALL have comprehensive unit tests for reverse proxy.\n596: \n597: #### Scenario: TestReverseProxy_Director\n598: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/reverse_proxy_test.go`\n599: - **WHEN** running tests\n600: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n601:   - Path normalization adds leading slash\n602:   - Forwarding headers are set\n603:   - JWT is injected\n604: \n605: #### Scenario: TestReverseProxy_ModifyResponse\n606: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/reverse_proxy_test.go`\n607: - **WHEN** running tests\n608: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n609:   - Session ID header added to response\n610: \n611: #### Scenario: TestReverseProxy_ErrorHandler\n612: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/reverse_proxy_test.go`\n613: - **WHEN** running tests\n614: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n615:   - Connection refused → 502\n616:   - Timeout → 504\n617:   - Other errors → 500\n618: \n619: ---\n620: \n621: ### Requirement: Unit tests for JWTManager\n622: \n623: The system SHALL have comprehensive unit tests for JWT operations.\n624: \n625: #### Scenario: TestJWTManager_GenerateToken\n626: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/jwt_test.go`\n627: - **WHEN** running tests\n628: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n629:   - Token contains correct claims\n630:   - Token is signed with RS256\n631:   - Token expires in 5 minutes\n632: \n633: #### Scenario: TestJWTManager_RSAKeyGeneration\n634: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/jwt_test.go`\n635: - **WHEN** running tests\n636: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n637:   - Key size is 2048 bits\n638:   - Keys are valid RSA keys\n639: \n640: #### Scenario: TestJWTManager_TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret\n641: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/jwt_test.go`\n642: - **WHEN** running tests\n643: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n644:   - Secret created when not exists\n645:   - Secret loaded when exists\n646:   - AlreadyExists handled gracefully\n647: \n648: ---\n649: \n650: ### Requirement: Unit tests for Middleware\n651: \n652: The system SHALL have comprehensive unit tests for concurrency middleware.\n653: \n654: #### Scenario: TestConcurrencyLimitMiddleware\n655: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/middleware_test.go`\n656: - **WHEN** running tests\n657: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n658:   - Requests proceed when slots available\n659:   - 429 returned when full\n660:   - Slots released after request completes\n661: \n662: #### Scenario: TestConcurrencyLimitMiddleware_DefaultCapacity\n663: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/middleware_test.go`\n664: - **WHEN** running tests with MaxConcurrentRequests <= 0\n665: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n666:   - Capacity defaults to 1000\n667: \n668: ---\n669: \n670: ### Requirement: Unit tests for Handlers\n671: \n672: The system SHALL have comprehensive unit tests for handlers.\n673: \n674: #### Scenario: TestHandleHealthLive\n675: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/handlers_test.go`\n676: - **WHEN** running tests\n677: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n678:   - Returns 200 with {\"status\":\"alive\"}\n679: \n680: #### Scenario: TestHandleHealthReady\n681: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/handlers_test.go`\n682: - **WHEN** running tests\n683: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n684:   - Returns 200 when sessionManager valid\n685:   - Returns 503 when sessionManager nil\n686: \n687: #### Scenario: TestHandleInvoke\n688: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/handlers_test.go`\n689: - **WHEN** running tests\n690: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n691:   - Session ID extracted from header\n692:   - New session created when missing\n693:   - Request proxied to sandbox endpoint\n694:   - Activity timestamp updated\n695: \n696: ---\n697: \n698: ### Requirement: Unit tests for Errors\n699: \n700: The system SHALL have comprehensive unit tests for error types.\n701: \n702: #### Scenario: TestErrorTypes\n703: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/errors_test.go`\n704: - **WHEN** running tests\n705: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n706:   - All error types implement APIStatus\n707:   - Status codes are correct\n708:   - Error codes are correct\n709: \n710: ---\n711: \n712: ### Requirement: File structure\n713: \n714: The system SHALL organize router files correctly.\n715: \n716: #### Scenario: server.go location\n717: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/`\n718: - **WHEN** listing files\n719: - **THEN** `server.go` SHALL exist with Server implementation\n720: \n721: #### Scenario: config.go location\n722: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/`\n723: - **WHEN** listing files\n724: - **THEN** `config.go` SHALL exist with Config struct\n725: \n726: #### Scenario: session_manager.go location\n727: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/`\n728: - **WHEN** listing files\n729: - **THEN** `session_manager.go` SHALL exist with SessionManager\n730: \n731: #### Scenario: reverse_proxy.go location\n732: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/`\n733: - **WHEN** listing files\n734: - **THEN** `reverse_proxy.go` SHALL exist with proxy implementation\n735: \n736: #### Scenario: jwt.go location\n737: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/`\n738: - **WHEN** listing files\n739: - **THEN** `jwt.go` SHALL exist with JWTManager\n740: \n741: #### Scenario: middleware.go location\n742: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/`\n743: - **WHEN** listing files\n744: - **THEN** `middleware.go` SHALL exist with concurrency middleware\n745: \n746: #### Scenario: handlers.go location\n747: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/`\n748: - **WHEN** listing files\n749: - **THEN** `handlers.go` SHALL exist with health and invocation handlers\n750: \n751: #### Scenario: errors.go location\n752: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/`\n753: - **WHEN** listing files\n754: - **THEN** `errors.go` SHALL exist with error types\n755: \n756: #### Scenario: Test files location\n757: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/`\n758: - **WHEN** listing files\n759: - **THEN** `*_test.go` SHALL exist for each implementation file\n760: \n761: ---\n762: \n763: ## Implementation Files\n764: \n765: | File | Purpose |\n766: |------|---------|\n767: | `pkg/router/server.go` | HTTP Server with Gin engine, route registration, lifecycle |\n768: | `pkg/router/server_test.go` | Server unit tests |\n769: | `pkg/router/config.go` | Config struct with Port, TLS, MaxConcurrentRequests |\n770: | `pkg/router/config_test.go` | Config unit tests |\n771: | `pkg/router/session_manager.go` | SessionManager interface and implementation |\n772: | `pkg/router/session_manager_test.go` | SessionManager unit tests |\n773: | `pkg/router/reverse_proxy.go` | Reverse proxy with Director, ModifyResponse, ErrorHandler |\n774: | `pkg/router/reverse_proxy_test.go` | Reverse proxy unit tests |\n775: | `pkg/router/jwt.go` | JWTManager with RSA key generation, token signing |\n776: | `pkg/router/jwt_test.go` | JWT unit tests |\n777: | `pkg/router/middleware.go` | Concurrency limit middleware |\n778: | `pkg/router/middleware_test.go` | Middleware unit tests |\n779: | `pkg/router/handlers.go` | Health and invocation handlers |\n780: | `pkg/router/handlers_test.go` | Handlers unit tests |\n781: | `pkg/router/errors.go` | Error types with APIStatus interface |\n782: | `pkg/router/errors_test.go` | Error types unit tests |\n783: | `pkg/router/doc.go` | Package documentation |\n784: \n785: ---\n786: \n787: ## Dependencies\n788: \n789: | Package | Purpose |\n790: |---------|---------|\n791: | `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | HTTP framework for routing and middleware |\n792: | `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | RS256 JWT signing |\n793: | `golang.org/x/net/http2` | h2c server configuration |\n794: | `net/http/httputil` | ReverseProxy for request forwarding |\n795: | `crypto/rsa` | RSA key generation and signing |\n796: | `k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes` | Core Kubernetes API for Secret management |\n797: | `pkg/common/types` | SandboxInfo, CreateSandboxRequest/Response, kind constants |\n798: | `pkg/store` | Store interface for session lookup and activity updates |\n799: \n800: ---\n801: \n802: ## Request Flow\n803: \n804: ```\n805: Client Request\n806: │\n807: ├── Middleware Chain\n808: │   ├── concurrencyLimitMiddleware (semaphore acquire)\n809: │   ├── loggingMiddleware\n810: │   └── recoveryMiddleware\n811: │\n812: ├── Handler: handleInvoke\n813: │   ├── Extract session ID from x-agentcube-session-id header\n814: │   ├── If missing: Generate new session ID\n815: │   │\n816: │   ├── SessionManager.GetSandboxBySession\n817: │   │   ├── Check store for existing session\n818: │   │   ├── If not found: createSandbox\n819: │   │   │   ├── POST to Workload Manager\n820: │   │   │   │   ├── /v1/agent-runtime (AgentRuntime)\n821: │   │   │   │   └── /v1/code-interpreter (CodeInterpreter)\n822: │   │   │   ├── With K8s SA token if available\n823: │   │   │   └── Store sandbox info\n824: │   │   └── Update activity timestamp (1st)\n825: │   │\n826: │   ├── ReverseProxy.ServeHTTP\n827: │   │   ├── Director\n828: │   │   │   ├── Path normalization (add leading slash)\n829: │   │   │   ├── Set Host, X-Forwarded-For, X-Real-IP\n830: │   │   │   ├── JWTManager.GenerateToken → Authorization header\n831: │   │   │   └── Target: SandboxInfo.EntryPoints[0].Endpoint\n832: │   │   ├── Forward to sandbox pod\n833: │   │   ├── ModifyResponse\n834: │   │   │   └── Add x-agentcube-session-id header\n835: │   │   └── ErrorHandler\n836: │   │       ├── Connection refused → 502\n837: │   │       └── Timeout → 504\n838: │   │\n839: │   └── Update activity timestamp (2nd)\n840: │\n841: └── Middleware Chain (exit)\n842:     └── concurrencyLimitMiddleware (semaphore release)\n843: ```\n844: \n845: ---\n846: \n847: ## Error Mapping\n848: \n849: | Error Type | HTTP Status | Error Code | Condition |\n850: |------------|-------------|------------|-----------|\n851: | `SessionNotFoundError` | 404 | `SESSION_NOT_FOUND` | Session not in store |\n852: | `SandboxUnreachableError` | 502 | `SANDBOX_UNREACHABLE` | Connection refused to pod |\n853: | `TimeoutError` | 504 | `SANDBOX_TIMEOUT` | Proxy timeout |\n854: | `JWTSigningFailedError` | 500 | `JWT_SIGNING_FAILED` | JWT generation failure |\n855: | `ServerOverloadedError` | 429 | `SERVER_OVERLOADED` | Semaphore full |\n856: | `NoEntryPointError` | 404 | `NO_ENTRY_POINT` | Empty EntryPoints array |\n857: \n858: ---\n859: \n860: ## Configuration Values\n861: \n862: | Parameter | Default | Source | Description |\n863: |-----------|---------|--------|-------------|\n864: | `Port` | 8080 | Config | Listening port |\n865: | `EnableTLS` | false | Config | TLS enablement |\n866: | `TLSCert` | \"\" | Config | Certificate file path |\n867: | `TLSKey` | \"\" | Config | Private key file path |\n868: | `MaxConcurrentRequests` | 1000 | Config | Semaphore capacity |\n869: | `ReadTimeout` | 30s | Server | HTTP read timeout |\n870: | `IdleTimeout` | 90s | Server | HTTP idle timeout |\n871: | `ShutdownTimeout` | 10s | Server | Graceful shutdown deadline |\n872: | `rsaKeySize` | 2048 | Const | RSA key bits |\n873: | `jwtExpiration` | 5m | Const | JWT validity duration |\n874: | `IdentitySecretName` | picod-router-identity | Const | JWT Secret name |\n875: | `HttpClientTimeout` | 2m | SessionManager | HTTP client timeout |\n876: | `MaxIdleConnsPerHost` | 100 | SessionManager | Connection pool size |\n877: | `HTTP2ReadIdleTimeout` | 30s | SessionManager | HTTP2 read idle |\n878: | `HTTP2PingTimeout` | 15s | SessionManager | HTTP2 ping timeout |\n879: \n880: ---\n881: \n882: ## Environment Variables\n883: \n884: | Variable | Required | Default | Usage |\n885: |----------|----------|---------|-------|\n886: | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | Yes | - | Workload Manager service URL |\n887: | `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` | No | default | Namespace for sandbox creation |\n888: \n889: ---\n890: \n891: ## Validation Checklist\n892: \n893: - [ ] Server struct defined with all required fields\n894: - [ ] Config struct with Port, TLS, MaxConcurrentRequests\n895: - [ ] NewServer constructor initializes Gin engine\n896: - [ ] Gin mode set based on Debug config\n897: - [ ] Server.Start supports TLS and non-TLS\n898: - [ ] Graceful shutdown with 10s deadline\n899: - [ ] Health routes registered (/health/live, /health/ready)\n900: - [ ] Invocation routes registered with GET and POST\n901: - [ ] Middleware chain applied (concurrency, logging, recovery)\n902: - [ ] SessionManager interface defined\n903: - [ ] GetSandboxBySession resolves or creates sessions\n904: - [ ] createSandbox POST to Workload Manager\n905: - [ ] K8s SA token added for in-cluster auth\n906: - [ ] ReverseProxy with custom Director\n907: - [ ] Director normalizes path and injects JWT\n908: - [ ] ModifyResponse adds session header\n909: - [ ] ErrorHandler maps errors to HTTP codes\n910: - [ ] JWTManager with RSA key generation\n911: - [ ] GenerateToken with RS256, 5m expiration\n912: - [ ] TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret handles creation/loading\n913: - [ ] AlreadyExists handled for concurrent routers\n914: - [ ] concurrencyLimitMiddleware with semaphore\n915: - [ ] 429 returned when overloaded\n916: - [ ] handleHealthLive returns 200\n917: - [ ] handleHealthReady checks sessionManager\n918: - [ ] handleInvoke proxies to sandbox\n919: - [ ] Activity timestamp updated twice\n920: - [ ] Error types implement APIStatus\n921: - [ ] WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL required\n922: - [ ] AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE with default\n923: - [ ] Constants defined (rsaKeySize, jwtExpiration, IdentitySecretName)\n924: - [ ] Unit tests for all components\n925: - [ ] Pass `go vet` with zero issues\n926: - [ ] Pass `golangci-lint` with zero issues\n927: - [ ] Unit tests pass with >80% coverage\n\n(End of file - total 927 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-009 — Router HTTP 反向代理核心\n\n**Module:** `pkg/router`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nDefine the HTTP reverse proxy core for the AgentCube Router component. This provides session-aware routing that resolves session IDs from request headers, creates sandboxes via Workload Manager, forwards HTTP requests to sandbox pod endpoints using `httputil.ReverseProxy`, generates RS256-signed JWT tokens, updates session activity timestamps, and limits concurrent requests via semaphore middleware.\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n### Requirement: Server type definition\n\nThe system SHALL define `Server` as an HTTP server with Gin engine for reverse proxy routing.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-009/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775850546578,"end":1775850546619}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775850546625,"sessionID":"ses_2870f54e9ffeZYvuDZque7APgc","part":{"id":"prt_d78f0ddc20016hmOC44o0qmWtf","messageID":"msg_d78f0c0e1001bSz0Cg2Sk2RjeW","sessionID":"ses_2870f54e9ffeZYvuDZque7APgc","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-8013d7e0ec6f49a78668b62b2e7e2013","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-009/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-009/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-009 — Router HTTP 反向代理核心 Proposal\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Implement the HTTP reverse proxy core for the AgentCube Router component. This provides session-aware routing that:\n6: \n7: 1. **Session Resolution**: Reads session ID from request header `x-agentcube-session-id`, creates new sandboxes via Workload Manager when missing\n8: 2. **Reverse Proxy**: Forwards HTTP requests to sandbox pod endpoints using `httputil.ReverseProxy`\n9: 3. **JWT Authentication**: Generates RS256-signed JWT tokens for `Sandbox` and `SandboxClaim` kinds\n10: 4. **Activity Tracking**: Updates session last-activity timestamps in the store for idle timeout detection\n11: 5. **Concurrency Control**: Limits concurrent requests via semaphore middleware to prevent overload\n12: 6. **Health Endpoints**: Exposes `/health/live` and `/health/ready` for Kubernetes probes\n13: \n14: ## Scope\n15: \n16: ### In Scope\n17: \n18: | Deliverable | Description |\n19: |-------------|-------------|\n20: | `pkg/router/server.go` | HTTP Server with Gin engine, route registration, lifecycle management |\n21: | `pkg/router/config.go` | Config struct (Port, EnableTLS, TLSCert, TLSKey, MaxConcurrentRequests, Debug) |\n22: | `pkg/router/session_manager.go` | SessionManager interface, manager struct with workload manager client |\n23: | `pkg/router/reverse_proxy.go` | Reverse proxy with custom Director, ModifyResponse, ErrorHandler |\n24: | `pkg/router/jwt.go` | JWTManager with RSA key generation, token signing, K8s Secret persistence |\n25: | `pkg/router/handlers.go` | `/health/live`, `/health/ready`, `/v1/...invocations/*path` handlers |\n26: | `pkg/router/middleware.go` | Concurrency limit middleware using buffered channel semaphore |\n27: | `pkg/router/errors.go` | Error types: SessionNotFoundError, SandboxUnreachableError, TimeoutError |\n28: | `pkg/router/server_test.go` | Server construction, route registration, TLS, health endpoints tests |\n29: | `pkg/router/session_manager_test.go` | Session resolution, workload manager create, error mapping tests |\n30: | `pkg/router/reverse_proxy_test.go` | Proxy director, forwarding headers, path normalization tests |\n31: | `pkg/router/jwt_test.go` | JWT generation, RS256 signing, secret persistence tests |\n32: \n33: ### Key Components\n34: \n35: ```\n36: pkg/router/\n37: ├── Server (server.go)\n38: │   ├── Config struct (Port, TLS, MaxConcurrentRequests, Debug)\n39: │   ├── gin.Engine setup with mode (Debug/Release)\n40: │   ├── Route registration (health, invocation routes)\n41: │   ├── http.Server with h2c, ReadTimeout 30s, IdleTimeout 90s\n42: │   ├── Start(ctx) with graceful shutdown (10s deadline)\n43: │   └── Dependencies: SessionManager, Store, JWTManager, http.Transport\n44: │\n45: ├── SessionManager (session_manager.go)\n46: │   ├── Interface: GetSandboxBySession(ctx, sessionID, namespace, name, kind)\n47: │   ├── manager struct with storeClient, workloadMgrAddr, httpClient\n48: │   ├── NewSessionManager: reads WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL (required)\n49: │   ├── createSandbox: POST to Workload Manager with optional K8s SA token\n50: │   └── HTTP client: Timeout 2m, MaxIdleConnsPerHost 100, HTTP2 config\n51: │\n52: ├── Reverse Proxy (reverse_proxy.go)\n53: │   ├── httputil.NewSingleHostReverseProxy\n54: │   ├── Director: path normalization, Host, forwarding headers, JWT\n55: │   ├── ModifyResponse: x-agentcube-session-id header injection\n56: │   ├── ErrorHandler: connection refused → 502, timeout → 504\n57: │   └── Entry point matching from SandboxInfo.EntryPoints\n58: │\n59: ├── JWT Manager (jwt.go)\n60: │   ├── RSA 2048-bit key generation (PKCS1 private, PKIX public)\n61: │   ├── GenerateToken: exp (5m), iat, iss=\"agentcube-router\", custom claims\n62: │   ├── TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret: K8s Secret persistence/reuse\n63: │   └── RS256 signing with golang-jwt/v5\n64: │\n65: ├── Middleware (middleware.go)\n66: │   ├── concurrencyLimitMiddleware: buffered channel semaphore\n67: │   ├── MaxConcurrentRequests capacity (default 1000 when ≤0)\n68: │   └── 429 response when overloaded: SERVER_OVERLOADED code\n69: │\n70: └── Handlers (handlers.go)\n71:     ├── handleHealthLive: 200 {\"status\":\"alive\"}\n72:     ├── handleHealthReady: 200/503 based on sessionManager nil\n73:     ├── handleInvoke: session resolution → proxy → activity update\n74:     └── Error mapping: APIStatus → appropriate HTTP code\n75: ```\n76: \n77: ### Out of Scope\n78: \n79: - Workload Manager implementation (covered by AR-00x)\n80: - Store implementation (covered by session-store spec)\n81: - Kubernetes Reconciler (AR-007)\n82: - Prometheus metrics export\n83: - Distributed session cache (Redis cluster)\n84: - WebSocket upgrade handling\n85: - Custom retry logic for failed proxies\n86: \n87: ## Impact Analysis\n88: \n89: ### Upstream Dependencies\n90: \n91: | Dependency | Impact |\n92: |------------|--------|\n93: | `pkg/store` | Store interface for session lookup, UpdateSessionLastActivity |\n94: | `pkg/common/types` | SandboxInfo, CreateSandboxRequest/Response, kind constants |\n95: | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` | AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter CR types |\n96: | `client-go` | kubernetes.Interface for JWT Secret management |\n97: | `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | HTTP framework for routing and middleware |\n98: | `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | RS256 JWT signing |\n99: | `golang.org/x/net/http2` | h2c server configuration |\n100: | Workload Manager service | POST `/v1/agent-runtime`, `/v1/code-interpreter` for sandbox creation |\n101: \n102: ### Downstream Consumers\n103: \n104: | Consumer | Usage |\n105: |----------|-------|\n106: | `cmd/router/main.go` | CLI entry point, flag parsing, Server construction |\n107: | Kubernetes Deployment | Router as reverse proxy front-end to sandbox pods |\n108: | SDK/CLI clients | Invocation requests routed through Router |\n109: | `pkg/agentd` (idle cleanup) | Last-activity timestamps for idle detection |\n110: | Kubernetes probes | `/health/live`, `/health/ready` endpoints |\n111: \n112: ### Breaking Change Considerations\n113: \n114: - **Session Header Name**: `x-agentcube-session-id` header is contract; changing breaks all clients\n115: - **JWT Secret Name**: `picod-router-identity` Secret; migration needed if renamed\n116: - **Invocation Route Pattern**: `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path` is fixed\n117: - **Response Header**: `x-agentcube-session-id` on proxied responses is client expectation\n118: - **Default Concurrency Limit**: 1000 when `MaxConcurrentRequests ≤ 0`; affects throughput under load\n119: \n120: ## Alternatives Considered\n121: \n122: ### Alternative 1: Envoy Sidecar Proxy\n123: \n124: **Approach**: Deploy Envoy as sidecar to handle routing and load balancing.\n125: \n126: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n127: |--------|------------|\n128: | Pros | Production-grade proxy; rich routing features; observability built-in |\n129: | Cons | Heavy sidecar; no session-aware routing; requires xDS control plane; JWT signing complex |\n130: \n131: **Decision**: Rejected. Session-aware routing requires custom logic that Envoy cannot natively provide. In-process Go reverse proxy offers tighter integration with session management.\n132: \n133: ### Alternative 2: Nginx Ingress with Lua\n134: \n135: **Approach**: Use Nginx Ingress with Lua scripts for session routing and JWT injection.\n136: \n137: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n138: |--------|------------|\n139: | Pros | High performance; widely deployed; Nginx ecosystem |\n140: | Cons | Lua scripting complexity; no native store integration; debugging harder; JWT requires external helper |\n141: \n142: **Decision**: Rejected. Go-based proxy provides native integration with `pkg/store`, `pkg/common/types`, and Kubernetes client-go. Lua-based approach lacks tight coupling needed for session lifecycle.\n143: \n144: ### Alternative 3: API Gateway (Kong/Traefik)\n145: \n146: **Approach**: Use Kong or Traefik as API gateway for routing.\n147: \n148: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n149: |--------|------------|\n150: | Pros | Plugin ecosystem; declarative config; multi-protocol support |\n151: | Cons | External dependency; session store integration via plugin; JWT plugin limitations |\n152: \n153: **Decision**: Rejected. AgentCube requires session-stateful routing with direct store access. External gateway adds operational complexity and latency.\n154: \n155: ### Alternative 4: Custom HTTP Router with FastHTTP\n156: \n157: **Approach**: Use `fasthttp` instead of `net/http` for higher performance.\n158: \n159: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n160: |--------|------------|\n161: | Pros | Lower latency; zero-allocation design; high throughput |\n162: | Cons | Different API from `net/http`; httputil.ReverseProxy incompatible; Gin ecosystem mismatch |\n163: \n164: **Decision**: Rejected. `net/http` compatibility is required for `httputil.ReverseProxy` and Kubernetes client libraries. Gin middleware ecosystem (cors, recovery) is well-supported. Performance targets met with current stack.\n165: \n166: ### Alternative 5: Session-less Direct Routing\n167: \n168: **Approach**: Clients directly invoke sandbox pods without session abstraction.\n169: \n170: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n171: |--------|------------|\n172: | Pros | No session state; simpler architecture |\n173: | Cons | Clients must track pod endpoints; no idle timeout; no JWT injection; breaks SDK abstraction |\n174: \n175: **Decision**: Rejected. Session abstraction is core to AgentCube design—clients use logical names (namespace/name) while Router handles physical routing (pod IPs) and lifecycle (creation/expiry).\n176: \n177: ## Risks\n178: \n179: | Risk | Mitigation |\n180: |------|------------|\n181: | Sandbox pod unreachable (connection refused) | ErrorHandler maps to 502 `sandbox unreachable` |\n182: | Sandbox timeout during proxy | ErrorHandler maps to 504 `sandbox timeout` |\n183: | JWT signing failure | Respond 500 with `JWT_SIGNING_FAILED` code |\n184: | Workload Manager unavailable | Startup fails if `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` missing; retry logic in session manager |\n185: | Secret creation race (multiple routers) | `AlreadyExists` handled by loading existing secret |\n186: | Concurrency limit exhaustion | 429 with `SERVER_OVERLOADED` code; client retry |\n187: | TLS misconfiguration | Start returns error if cert/key missing when `EnableTLS=true` |\n188: | Session not found in store | 404 with `SessionNotFoundError` |\n189: | Entry points empty | 404 `no entry point found for sandbox` |\n190: | Path normalization missing leading slash | Director prefixes `/` if needed |\n191: \n192: ## Implementation Notes\n193: \n194: 1. **Constants**: `rsaKeySize=2048`, `jwtExpiration=5m`, `IdentitySecretName=\"picod-router-identity\"`\n195: 2. **HTTP2**: `h2c` server with `http2.Server` for non-TLS HTTP/2 support\n196: 3. **Transport**: `IdleConnTimeout=0`, `DisableCompression=false`, shared across all proxies\n197: 4. **Session Manager HTTP Client**: `Timeout=2m`, `MaxIdleConnsPerHost=100`, HTTP2 with `ReadIdleTimeout=30s`, `PingTimeout=15s`\n198: 5. **Workload Manager Auth**: Reads `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` for in-cluster auth\n199: 6. **Environment Variables**: `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` (required), `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` (optional, default=\"default\")\n200: 7. **Last-Activity Updates**: Twice per invoke—after sandbox resolution and after proxy completion\n201: 8. **Graceful Shutdown**: 10s deadline on context cancel\n202: 9. **Route Pattern**: Both GET and POST on invocation routes\n203: \n204: ## References\n205: \n206: - `session-routing/spec.md` - Full requirement specification\n207: - `session-routing/design.md` - Detailed design document\n208: - `pkg/common/types/sandbox.go` - SandboxInfo, CreateSandboxRequest/Response types\n209: - `deployment/client-go.md` - Kubernetes client code reference\n210: - `project.md` - AgentCube architecture overview\n211: - `httputil.ReverseProxy`: https://pkg.go.dev/net/http/httputil#ReverseProxy\n212: - `golang-jwt/v5`: https://github.com/golang-jwt/jwt\n\n(End of file - total 212 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-009 — Router HTTP 反向代理核心 Proposal\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement the HTTP reverse proxy core for the AgentCube Router component. This provides session-aware routing that:\n\n1. **Session Resolution**: Reads session ID from request header `x-agentcube-session-id`, creates new sandboxes via Workload Manager when missing\n2. **Reverse Proxy**: Forwards HTTP requests to sandbox pod endpoints using `httputil.ReverseProxy`\n3. **JWT Authentication**: Generates RS256-signed JWT tokens for `Sandbox` and `SandboxClaim` kinds\n4. **Activity Tracking**: Updates session last-activity timestamps in the store for idle timeout detection\n5. **Concurrency Control**: Limits concurrent requests via semaphore middleware to prevent overload\n6. **Health Endpoints**: Exposes `/health/live` and `/health/ready` for Kubernetes probes\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n| Deliverable | Description |\n|-------------|-------------|\n| `pkg/router/server.go` | HTTP Server with Gin engine, route registration, lifecycle management |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-009/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775850546581,"end":1775850546623}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775850546629,"sessionID":"ses_2870f54e9ffeZYvuDZque7APgc","part":{"id":"prt_d78f0e184001AFXN9GWwmlcjvP","messageID":"msg_d78f0c0e1001bSz0Cg2Sk2RjeW","sessionID":"ses_2870f54e9ffeZYvuDZque7APgc","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-f1e77693e3ef4280958286cc966dd709","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-009/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-009/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-009 — Router HTTP 反向代理核心 Design\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-009 — Router HTTP 反向代理核心 |\n8: | Module | `pkg/router` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Stage | ST-1 |\n12: \n13: The Router HTTP reverse proxy core provides session-aware routing for AgentCube sandbox invocations. It resolves sessions via the store, creates new sandboxes through the Workload Manager when needed, reverse-proxies HTTP requests to sandbox pod endpoints, injects JWT tokens for sandbox authentication, and tracks activity for idle timeout detection.\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## Architecture\n18: \n19: ### System Context\n20: \n21: ```\n22: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n23: │                              AgentCube Cluster                               │\n24: │  ┌─────────────┐                                                             │\n25: │  │ Client/SDK  │                                                             │\n26: │  └──────┬──────┘                                                             │\n27: │         │ HTTP + x-agentcube-session-id                                      │\n28: │         ▼                                                                     │\n29: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n30: │  │                        Router (pkg/router)                              │ │\n31: │  │  ┌─────────────┐  ┌───────────────┐  ┌────────────┐  ┌───────────────┐  │ │\n32: │  │  │   Server    │  │SessionManager │  │JWTManager  │  │ ReverseProxy  │  │ │\n33: │  │  │  (Gin)      │  │               │  │            │  │               │  │ │\n34: │  │  └──────┬──────┘  └───────┬───────┘  └─────┬──────┘  └───────┬───────┘  │ │\n35: │  │         │                 │                 │                 │          │ │\n36: │  │  ┌──────▼─────────────────▼─────────────────▼─────────────────▼──────┐  │ │\n37: │  │  │                     Middleware Stack                               │  │ │\n38: │  │  │  Logger → Recovery → ConcurrencyLimit                              │  │ │\n39: │  │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │ │\n40: │  └──────────┬────────────────────────────────────┬──────────────────────────┘ │\n41: │             │                                    │                            │\n42: │             ▼                                    ▼                            │\n43: │  ┌──────────────────┐               ┌────────────────────────────┐            │\n44: │  │  Redis/Valkey    │               │    Workload Manager        │            │\n45: │  │  (Session Store) │               │    (Sandbox Creation)      │            │\n46: │  └──────────────────┘               └─────────────┬──────────────┘            │\n47: │                                                     │                         │\n48: │                                                     ▼                         │\n49: │                                      ┌────────────────────────────┐           │\n50: │                                      │  Kubernetes API Server     │           │\n51: │                                      │  (CRDs, Pods, Secrets)     │           │\n52: │                                      └─────────────┬──────────────┘           │\n53: │                                                    │                          │\n54: │                                                    ▼                          │\n55: │                                      ┌────────────────────────────┐           │\n56: │                                      │      Sandbox Pods          │           │\n57: │                                      │  (Target Endpoints)        │           │\n58: │                                      └────────────────────────────┘           │\n59: │  └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n60: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n61: ```\n62: \n63: ### Request Flow\n64: \n65: ```\n66: 1. Client Request → Router Server\n67:    │\n68: 2. Middleware Chain (Logger → Recovery → ConcurrencyLimit)\n69:    │\n70: 3. Route Handler (handleInvoke)\n71:    │\n72: 4. Session Resolution (SessionManager.GetSandboxBySession)\n73:    ├─ Header present → Store lookup\n74:    └─ Header empty → Workload Manager POST → Store save\n75:    │\n76: 5. Last-Activity Update (store.UpdateSessionLastActivity)\n77:    │\n78: 6. Entry Point Selection (SandboxInfo.EntryPoints matching)\n79:    │\n80: 7. JWT Generation (JWTManager.GenerateToken) [for Sandbox/SandboxClaim]\n81:    │\n82: 8. Reverse Proxy (httputil.ReverseProxy)\n83:    ├─ Director: path normalization, forwarding headers, JWT\n84:    └─ ErrorHandler: 502/504 error mapping\n85:    │\n86: 9. Response Header Injection (x-agentcube-session-id)\n87:    │\n88: 10. Last-Activity Update (after proxy completion)\n89:    │\n90: 11. Response → Client\n91: ```\n92: \n93: ---\n94: \n95: ## Design\n96: \n97: ### Component Relationships\n98: \n99: | Component | Role | Dependencies |\n100: |-----------|------|--------------|\n101: | `Server` | Gin HTTP server, route registration, lifecycle management | `SessionManager`, `Store`, `JWTManager`, `http.Transport` |\n102: | `SessionManager` | Session resolution, sandbox creation via Workload Manager | `Store`, Workload Manager HTTP client |\n103: | `JWTManager` | RS256 JWT generation, K8s Secret persistence | `kubernetes.Interface`, RSA keys |\n104: | `ReverseProxy` | HTTP forwarding to sandbox pods, header injection | `http.Transport`, `JWTManager` |\n105: | `Middleware` | Concurrency limiting via semaphore | Config (`MaxConcurrentRequests`) |\n106: | `Handlers` | Health endpoints, invocation routing | `SessionManager`, `Store`, `ReverseProxy` |\n107: \n108: ### Dependencies\n109: \n110: | Package | Purpose | Import Path |\n111: |---------|---------|-------------|\n112: | Gin | HTTP framework, routing, middleware | `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` |\n113: | JWT | RS256 JWT signing | `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` |\n114: | HTTP2 | h2c server configuration | `golang.org/x/net/http2` |\n115: | Client-go | Kubernetes API client | `k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes` |\n116: | Klog | Structured logging | `k8s.io/klog/v2` |\n117: | Store | Session storage interface | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store` |\n118: | Types | SandboxInfo, CreateSandboxRequest/Response | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` |\n119: | APIErrors | Kubernetes API status errors | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors` |\n120: \n121: ---\n122: \n123: ## Data Structures\n124: \n125: ### Config (`config.go`)\n126: \n127: ```go\n128: package router\n129: \n130: type Config struct {\n131:     Port                  string        // Listening port (e.g., \":8080\")\n132:     EnableTLS             bool          // Enable TLS\n133:     TLSCert               string        // TLS certificate file path\n134:     TLSKey                string        // TLS private key file path\n135:     MaxConcurrentRequests int           // Semaphore capacity (default 1000 when <=0)\n136:     Debug                 bool          // Gin debug mode\n137: }\n138: ```\n139: \n140: **Defaults:**\n141: - `Port`: `\":8080\"`\n142: - `MaxConcurrentRequests`: `1000` (when value <= 0 in `NewServer`)\n143: \n144: ### Server (`server.go`)\n145: \n146: ```go\n147: type Server struct {\n148:     config         *Config\n149:     engine         *gin.Engine\n150:     httpServer     *http.Server\n151:     sessionManager SessionManager\n152:     storeClient    store.Store\n153:     httpTransport  *http.Transport\n154:     jwtManager     *JWTManager\n155: }\n156: ```\n157: \n158: **HTTP Server Configuration:**\n159: - `ReadTimeout`: 30s\n160: - `IdleTimeout`: 90s\n161: - H2C enabled via `http2.Server`\n162: \n163: ### SessionManager (`session_manager.go`)\n164: \n165: ```go\n166: type SessionManager interface {\n167:     GetSandboxBySession(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, namespace string, name string, kind string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n168: }\n169: \n170: type manager struct {\n171:     storeClient     store.Store\n172:     workloadMgrAddr string\n173:     httpClient      *http.Client\n174: }\n175: ```\n176: \n177: **HTTP Client Configuration:**\n178: - `Timeout`: 2m\n179: - `MaxIdleConnsPerHost`: 100\n180: - `DisableCompression`: false\n181: - HTTP2: `ReadIdleTimeout=30s`, `PingTimeout=15s`\n182: \n183: ### JWTManager (`jwt.go`)\n184: \n185: ```go\n186: type JWTManager struct {\n187:     privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey\n188:     publicKey  *rsa.PublicKey\n189:     clientset  kubernetes.Interface\n190: }\n191: ```\n192: \n193: **Constants:**\n194: ```go\n195: const (\n196:     rsaKeySize          = 2048\n197:     jwtExpiration       = 5 * time.Minute\n198:     IdentitySecretName  = \"picod-router-identity\"\n199:     PrivateKeyDataKey   = \"private.pem\"\n200:     PublicKeyDataKey    = \"public.pem\"\n201: )\n202: \n203: var IdentityNamespace = \"default\" // init: AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE if set\n204: ```\n205: \n206: ### Error Types (`errors.go`)\n207: \n208: ```go\n209: type SessionNotFoundError struct {\n210:     SessionID string\n211: }\n212: \n213: type SandboxUnreachableError struct {\n214:     SandboxID string\n215: }\n216: \n217: type SandboxTimeoutError struct {\n218:     SandboxID string\n219: }\n220: \n221: type JWTSigningError struct {\n222:     Err error\n223: }\n224: \n225: type WorkloadManagerError struct {\n226:     StatusCode int\n227:     Message    string\n228: }\n229: ```\n230: \n231: ---\n232: \n233: ## API Contracts\n234: \n235: ### Route Table\n236: \n237: | Method | Path | Middleware | Handler |\n238: |--------|------|------------|---------|\n239: | GET | `/health/live` | none | `handleHealthLive` |\n240: | GET | `/health/ready` | none | `handleHealthReady` |\n241: | GET | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path` | Logger, Recovery, ConcurrencyLimit | `handleAgentInvoke` |\n242: | POST | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path` | Logger, Recovery, ConcurrencyLimit | `handleAgentInvoke` |\n243: | GET | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path` | Logger, Recovery, ConcurrencyLimit | `handleCodeInterpreterInvoke` |\n244: | POST | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path` | Logger, Recovery, ConcurrencyLimit | `handleCodeInterpreterInvoke` |\n245: \n246: ### Session Manager Interface\n247: \n248: ```go\n249: type SessionManager interface {\n250:     GetSandboxBySession(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, namespace string, name string, kind string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n251: }\n252: ```\n253: \n254: **Behavior:**\n255: - When `sessionID` is empty: POST to Workload Manager, store result, return `SandboxInfo`\n256: - When `sessionID` is non-empty: Lookup from store, return `SandboxInfo` or error\n257: \n258: **Workload Manager Endpoints:**\n259: - `AgentRuntime`: `{WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL}/v1/agent-runtime`\n260: - `CodeInterpreter`: `{WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL}/v1/code-interpreter`\n261: \n262: ### JWT Manager Interface\n263: \n264: ```go\n265: func NewJWTManager() (*JWTManager, error)\n266: func (j *JWTManager) GenerateToken(claims map[string]interface{}) (string, error)\n267: func (j *JWTManager) TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret(ctx context.Context) error\n268: ```\n269: \n270: **JWT Claims Structure:**\n271: ```go\n272: {\n273:     \"exp\": <now + 5m Unix>,\n274:     \"iat\": <now Unix>,\n275:     \"iss\": \"agentcube-router\",\n276:     // + custom claims (e.g., \"session_id\")\n277: }\n278: ```\n279: \n280: ### Health Endpoints\n281: \n282: **Live Check (`GET /health/live`):**\n283: ```json\n284: {\"status\": \"alive\"}\n285: ```\n286: Status: 200\n287: \n288: **Ready Check (`GET /health/ready`):**\n289: ```json\n290: {\"status\": \"ready\"}\n291: ```\n292: Status: 200 (when sessionManager != nil)\n293: \n294: ```json\n295: {\"status\": \"not ready\", \"error\": \"session manager not available\"}\n296: ```\n297: Status: 503 (when sessionManager == nil)\n298: \n299: ### Invocation Response Headers\n300: \n301: | Header | Value |\n302: |--------|-------|\n303: | `x-agentcube-session-id` | Resolved session ID |\n304: \n305: ### Error Response Format\n306: \n307: ```json\n308: {\n309:     \"error\": \"<message>\",\n310:     \"code\": \"<error_code>\"\n311: }\n312: ```\n313: \n314: **Error Codes:**\n315: | Code | HTTP Status | Condition |\n316: |------|-------------|-----------|\n317: | `SESSION_NOT_FOUND` | 404 | Store lookup failed |\n318: | `SANDBOX_UNREACHABLE` | 502 | Connection refused |\n319: | `SANDBOX_TIMEOUT` | 504 | Timeout during proxy |\n320: | `JWT_SIGNING_FAILED` | 500 | JWT generation failed |\n321: | `SERVER_OVERLOADED` | 429 | Concurrency limit exhausted |\n322: | `NO_ENTRY_POINT` | 404 | Empty EntryPoints in SandboxInfo |\n323: \n324: ---\n325: \n326: ## Error Handling\n327: \n328: ### Proxy Error Mapping (`reverse_proxy.go`)\n329: \n330: ```go\n331: func proxyErrorHandler(resp http.ResponseWriter, req *http.Request, err error) {\n332:     errMsg := err.Error()\n333:     var statusCode int\n334:     var message string\n335:     \n336:     if strings.Contains(errMsg, \"connection refused\") {\n337:         statusCode = http.StatusBadGateway\n338:         message = \"sandbox unreachable\"\n339:     } else if strings.Contains(errMsg, \"timeout\") {\n340:         statusCode = http.StatusGatewayTimeout\n341:         message = \"sandbox timeout\"\n342:     } else {\n343:         statusCode = http.StatusBadGateway\n344:         message = \"sandbox unreachable\"\n345:     }\n346:     \n347:     resp.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n348:     resp.WriteHeader(statusCode)\n349:     json.NewEncoder(resp).Encode(gin.H{\"error\": message})\n350: }\n351: ```\n352: \n353: ### Handler Error Helper (`handlers.go`)\n354: \n355: ```go\n356: func handleGetSandboxError(c *gin.Context, err error) {\n357:     if apierrors.IsNotFound(err) {\n358:         c.JSON(http.StatusNotFound, gin.H{\"error\": err.Error()})\n359:         return\n360:     }\n361:     \n362:     if apiStatus, ok := err.(apierrors.APIStatus); ok {\n363:         code := int(apiStatus.Status().Code)\n364:         if code == 0 {\n365:             code = http.StatusInternalServerError\n366:         }\n367:         msg := apiStatus.Status().Message\n368:         if msg == \"\" {\n369:             msg = err.Error()\n370:         }\n371:         if code == http.StatusInternalServerError {\n372:             msg = \"internal server error\"\n373:         }\n374:         c.JSON(code, gin.H{\"error\": msg})\n375:         return\n376:     }\n377:     \n378:     c.JSON(http.StatusInternalServerError, gin.H{\"error\": \"internal server error\"})\n379: }\n380: ```\n381: \n382: ### Workload Manager Response Handling\n383: \n384: | HTTP Status | Error Type |\n385: |-------------|------------|\n386: | 404 | `SandboxTemplateNotFoundError` |\n387: | Non-200 | `WorkloadManagerError` |\n388: | Empty `sessionId` in body | Internal error (validation) |\n389: \n390: ### Store Error Mapping\n391: \n392: | Store Error | HTTP Response |\n393: |-------------|---------------|\n394: | `store.ErrNotFound` | 404 with `SessionNotFoundError` |\n395: | Other errors | 500 internal server error |\n396: \n397: ---\n398: \n399: ## Reverse Proxy Implementation\n400: \n401: ### Director Function (`reverse_proxy.go`)\n402: \n403: ```go\n404: func director(req *http.Request, target *url.URL, jwt string) {\n405:     // Path normalization\n406:     path := req.URL.Path\n407:     if path != \"\" && path[0] != '/' {\n408:         path = \"/\" + path\n409:     }\n410:     \n411:     req.URL.Scheme = target.Scheme\n412:     req.URL.Host = target.Host\n413:     req.URL.Path = path\n414:     req.URL.RawPath = \"\"\n415:     req.Host = target.Host\n416:     \n417:     // Forwarding headers\n418:     req.Header.Set(\"X-Forwarded-Host\", req.Header.Get(\"Host\"))\n419:     proto := \"http\"\n420:     if req.TLS != nil {\n421:         proto = \"https\"\n422:     }\n423:     req.Header.Set(\"X-Forwarded-Proto\", proto)\n424:     \n425:     existingXFF := req.Header.Get(\"X-Forwarded-For\")\n426:     clientIP := req.RemoteAddr\n427:     if existingXFF != \"\" {\n428:         clientIP = existingXFF + \",\" + clientIP\n429:     }\n430:     req.Header.Set(\"X-Forwarded-For\", clientIP)\n431:     \n432:     // JWT injection\n433:     if jwt != \"\" {\n434:         req.Header.Set(\"Authorization\", \"Bearer \"+jwt)\n435:     }\n436: }\n437: ```\n438: \n439: ### Entry Point Selection\n440: \n441: ```go\n442: func selectEntryPoint(entryPoints []types.SandboxEntryPoint, invocationPath string) *types.SandboxEntryPoint {\n443:     if len(entryPoints) == 0 {\n444:         return nil\n445:     }\n446:     \n447:     // Find matching entry point by path prefix\n448:     for _, ep := range entryPoints {\n449:         if strings.HasPrefix(invocationPath, ep.Path) {\n450:             return &ep\n451:         }\n452:     }\n453:     \n454:     // Default to first entry point\n455:     return &entryPoints[0]\n456: }\n457: \n458: func buildTargetURL(ep *types.SandboxEntryPoint) *url.URL {\n459:     endpoint := ep.Endpoint\n460:     if ep.Protocol != \"\" && !strings.Contains(endpoint, \"://\") {\n461:         endpoint = strings.ToLower(ep.Protocol) + \"://\" + endpoint\n462:     }\n463:     return url.Parse(endpoint)\n464: }\n465: ```\n466: \n467: ---\n468: \n469: ## Middleware Implementation\n470: \n471: ### Concurrency Limit (`middleware.go`)\n472: \n473: ```go\n474: func concurrencyLimitMiddleware(maxConcurrent int) gin.HandlerFunc {\n475:     if maxConcurrent <= 0 {\n476:         maxConcurrent = 1000\n477:     }\n478:     \n479:     sem := make(chan struct{}, maxConcurrent)\n480:     \n481:     return func(c *gin.Context) {\n482:         select {\n483:         case sem <- struct{}{}:\n484:             defer func() { <-sem }()\n485:             c.Next()\n486:         default:\n487:             c.JSON(http.StatusTooManyRequests, gin.H{\n488:                 \"error\": \"server overloaded, please try again later\",\n489:                 \"code\":  \"SERVER_OVERLOADED\",\n490:             })\n491:             c.Abort()\n492:         }\n493:     }\n494: }\n495: ```\n496: \n497: ---\n498: \n499: ## JWT Implementation\n500: \n501: ### Token Generation (`jwt.go`)\n502: \n503: ```go\n504: func (j *JWTManager) GenerateToken(claims map[string]interface{}) (string, error) {\n505:     now := time.Now()\n506:     \n507:     token := jwt.NewWithClaims(jwt.SigningMethodRS256, jwt.MapClaims{\n508:         \"exp\": now.Add(jwtExpiration).Unix(),\n509:         \"iat\": now.Unix(),\n510:         \"iss\": \"agentcube-router\",\n511:     })\n512:     \n513:     // Merge custom claims\n514:     for k, v := range claims {\n515:         token.Claims.(jwt.MapClaims)[k] = v\n516:     }\n517:     \n518:     return token.SignedString(j.privateKey)\n519: }\n520: ```\n521: \n522: ### Secret Persistence\n523: \n524: ```go\n525: func (j *JWTManager) TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret(ctx context.Context) error {\n526:     if j.clientset == nil {\n527:         // Try in-cluster config\n528:         config, err := rest.InClusterConfig()\n529:         if err != nil {\n530:             klog.Warningf(\"not in cluster, skipping secret persistence: %v\", err)\n531:             return nil\n532:         }\n533:         j.clientset, err = kubernetes.NewForConfig(config)\n534:         if err != nil {\n535:             return err\n536:         }\n537:     }\n538:     \n539:     secret := &corev1.Secret{\n540:         ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n541:             Name:      IdentitySecretName,\n542:             Namespace: IdentityNamespace,\n543:             Labels: map[string]string{\n544:                 \"app\":       \"agentcube\",\n545:                 \"component\": \"router\",\n546:             },\n547:         },\n548:         Type: corev1.SecretTypeOpaque,\n549:         Data: map[string][]byte{\n550:             PrivateKeyDataKey: encodePrivateKeyPEM(j.privateKey),\n551:             PublicKeyDataKey:  encodePublicKeyPEM(j.publicKey),\n552:         },\n553:     }\n554:     \n555:     _, err := j.clientset.CoreV1().Secrets(IdentityNamespace).Create(ctx, secret, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n556:     if apierrors.IsAlreadyExists(err) {\n557:         existing, err := j.clientset.CoreV1().Secrets(IdentityNamespace).Get(ctx, IdentitySecretName, metav1.GetOptions{})\n558:         if err != nil {\n559:             return err\n560:         }\n561:         return j.loadPrivateKeyPEM(existing.Data[PrivateKeyDataKey])\n562:     }\n563:     return err\n564: }\n565: ```\n566: \n567: **Key Encoding:**\n568: - Private key: PKCS1 PEM format (`RSA PRIVATE KEY`)\n569: - Public key: PKIX PEM format (`PUBLIC KEY`)\n570: \n571: ---\n572: \n573: ## Testing Strategy\n574: \n575: ### Test Coverage Goals\n576: \n577: | Component | Coverage Target | Key Test Cases |\n578: |-----------|-----------------|----------------|\n579: | `Server` | 80% | Construction, route registration, TLS, graceful shutdown |\n580: | `SessionManager` | 85% | Session resolution, Workload Manager create, error mapping |\n581: | `JWTManager` | 80% | Token generation, RS256 signing, secret persistence |\n582: | `ReverseProxy` | 85% | Director, forwarding headers, path normalization, error handler |\n583: | `Handlers` | 80% | Health endpoints, invocation routing, error responses |\n584: | `Middleware` | 75% | Concurrency limit, 429 response |\n585: \n586: ### Test Files\n587: \n588: | File | Purpose |\n589: |------|---------|\n590: | `server_test.go` | Server construction, route registration, TLS, health checks |\n591: | `session_manager_test.go` | GetSandboxBySession, create via Workload Manager, error cases |\n592: | `jwt_test.go` | Token generation, RS256 verification, secret CRUD |\n593: | `reverse_proxy_test.go` | Director, path normalization, header injection, error mapping |\n594: | `handlers_test.go` | Health endpoints, invocation handlers |\n595: | `middleware_test.go` | Concurrency limit, overload response |\n596: | `errors_test.go` | Error type construction, message formatting |\n597: \n598: ### Mock Dependencies\n599: \n600: ```go\n601: type MockStore struct {\n602:     GetSandboxBySessionIDFunc  func(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n603:     StoreSandboxFunc           func(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error\n604:     UpdateSessionLastActivityFunc func(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n605: }\n606: \n607: type MockSessionManager struct {\n608:     GetSandboxBySessionFunc func(ctx context.Context, sessionID, namespace, name, kind string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n609: }\n610: \n611: type MockJWTManager struct {\n612:     GenerateTokenFunc func(claims map[string]interface{}) (string, error)\n613: }\n614: \n615: type MockHTTPClient struct {\n616:     DoFunc func(req *http.Request) (*http.Response, error)\n617: }\n618: ```\n619: \n620: ### Integration Test Scenarios\n621: \n622: 1. **Session Resolution Flow**\n623:    - Request without session header → creates sandbox via Workload Manager\n624:    - Request with valid session header → lookup from store\n625:    - Request with invalid session → 404 response\n626: \n627: 2. **Proxy Flow**\n628:    - Successful proxy → response header with session ID\n629:    - Sandbox unreachable → 502 response\n630:    - Sandbox timeout → 504 response\n631: \n632: 3. **JWT Injection**\n633:    - Sandbox/SandboxClaim kind → JWT in Authorization header\n634:    - AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter → no JWT\n635: \n636: 4. **Concurrency Limit**\n637:    - Under limit → request processed\n638:    - At limit → 429 response\n639: \n640: 5. **Graceful Shutdown**\n641:    - Context cancel → shutdown within 10s deadline\n642:    - Existing requests complete before shutdown\n643: \n644: ---\n645: \n646: ## Validation Checklist\n647: \n648: - [ ] Config validates required fields (Port non-empty)\n649: - [ ] TLS requires both cert and key when EnableTLS=true\n650: - [ ] SessionManager requires WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL env\n651: - [ ] JWTManager generates valid RS256 tokens (verified by public key)\n652: - [ ] ReverseProxy Director normalizes paths correctly\n653: - [ ] ErrorHandler maps connection refused → 502\n654: - [ ] ErrorHandler maps timeout → 504\n655: - [ ] Health endpoints return correct JSON shapes\n656: - [ ] Concurrency middleware defaults to 1000 when config <= 0\n657: - [ ] Last-activity updated twice per invocation\n658: - [ ] Entry point selection handles empty list\n659: - [ ] Response header x-agentcube-session-id injected\n660: - [ ] Forwarding headers set correctly\n661: - [ ] Graceful shutdown respects 10s deadline\n662: \n663: ---\n664: \n665: ## Open Questions\n666: \n667: 1. **JWT Secret Rotation**: How to handle key rotation without disrupting active sessions?\n668:    - Proposal: Load both old and new keys, accept tokens signed by either\n669: \n670: 2. **Workload Manager Retry**: Should failed sandbox creation be retried?\n671:    - Current: Single attempt, client must retry\n672:    - Alternative: Add exponential backoff retry in SessionManager\n673: \n674: 3. **WebSocket Support**: Should Router proxy WebSocket upgrades?\n675:    - Current: Not supported (out of scope)\n676:    - Future: Add WebSocket upgrade handling in reverse_proxy.go\n677: \n678: 4. **Metrics Export**: Prometheus metrics for proxy latency, error rates?\n679:    - Current: Not in scope\n680:    - Future: Add middleware to record request duration and status codes\n681: \n682: ---\n683: \n684: ## References\n685: \n686: - `session-routing/spec.md` — Full requirement specification\n687: - `session-routing/design.md` — Detailed design document  \n688: - `session-store/design.md` — Store interface and implementations\n689: - `pkg/common/types/sandbox.go` — SandboxInfo, CreateSandboxRequest/Response types\n690: - `deployment/client-go.md` — Kubernetes client code reference\n691: - `pkg/workloadmanager/server.go` — Workload Manager server pattern reference\n692: - `project.md` — AgentCube architecture overview\n693: - Go `httputil.ReverseProxy`: https://pkg.go.dev/net/http/httputil#ReverseProxy\n694: - `golang-jwt/v5`: https://github.com/golang-jwt/jwt\n695: - Gin framework: https://github.com/gin-gonic/gin\n\n(End of file - total 695 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-009 — Router HTTP 反向代理核心 Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-009 — Router HTTP 反向代理核心 |\n| Module | `pkg/router` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-1 |\n\nThe Router HTTP reverse proxy core provides session-aware routing for AgentCube sandbox invocations. It resolves sessions via the store, creates new sandboxes through the Workload Manager when needed, reverse-proxies HTTP requests to sandbox pod endpoints, injects JWT tokens for sandbox authentication, and tracks activity for idle timeout detection.\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### System Context\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-009/design.md","time":{"start":1775850546583,"end":1775850546626}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775850546633,"sessionID":"ses_2870f54e9ffeZYvuDZque7APgc","part":{"id":"prt_d78f0e536001TKHtFkHJr7YQhS","messageID":"msg_d78f0c0e1001bSz0Cg2Sk2RjeW","sessionID":"ses_2870f54e9ffeZYvuDZque7APgc","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-557d1646201e40f18215027bbed6deea","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-009/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-009/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-009 — Router HTTP 反向代理核心 Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Metadata\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-009 — Router HTTP 反向代理核心 |\n8: | Module | `pkg/router` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Task Checklist\n16: \n17: ### Phase 1: Error Types & Interfaces (ST-1)\n18: \n19: - [ ] **T1.1**: Define error types in `errors.go`\n20:   - `SessionNotFoundError` with `SessionID` field, code `SESSION_NOT_FOUND`, HTTP 404\n21:   - `SandboxUnreachableError` with `SandboxID` field, code `SANDBOX_UNREACHABLE`, HTTP 502\n22:   - `SandboxTimeoutError` with `SandboxID` field, code `SANDBOX_TIMEOUT`, HTTP 504\n23:   - `JWTSigningError` with `Err` field, code `JWT_SIGNING_FAILED`, HTTP 500\n24:   - `ServerOverloadedError` with code `SERVER_OVERLOADED`, HTTP 429\n25:   - `NoEntryPointError` with code `NO_ENTRY_POINT`, HTTP 404\n26:   - All errors implement `APIStatus` interface: `Status() int`, `Code() string`, `Message() string`\n27:   - File: `pkg/router/errors.go`\n28:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestErrorTypes -v`\n29: \n30: - [ ] **T1.2**: Define `APIStatus` interface\n31:   - Methods: `Status() int`, `Code() string`, `Message() string`\n32:   - All error types implement this interface\n33:   - File: `pkg/router/errors.go`\n34:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestAPIStatus -v`\n35: \n36: ### Phase 2: Config & Constants (ST-2)\n37: \n38: - [ ] **T2.1**: Define `Config` struct in `config.go`\n39:   - `Port int` (default 8080)\n40:   - `EnableTLS bool`\n41:   - `TLSCert string`\n42:   - `TLSKey string`\n43:   - `MaxConcurrentRequests int` (default 1000)\n44:   - `Debug bool`\n45:   - File: `pkg/router/config.go`\n46:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestConfig -v`\n47: \n48: - [ ] **T2.2**: Implement `DefaultConfig()` function\n49:   - Returns `Config{Port: 8080, EnableTLS: false, MaxConcurrentRequests: 1000}`\n50:   - File: `pkg/router/config.go`\n51:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestDefaultConfig -v`\n52: \n53: - [ ] **T2.3**: Define constants in `jwt.go`\n54:   - `rsaKeySize = 2048`\n55:   - `jwtExpiration = 5 * time.Minute`\n56:   - `IdentitySecretName = \"picod-router-identity\"`\n57:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n58:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestConstants -v`\n59: \n60: ### Phase 3: Store Interface & Logger (ST-3)\n61: \n62: - [ ] **T3.1**: Define `Store` interface for router\n63:   - `GetSession(ctx, sessionID) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n64:   - `CreateSession(ctx, sandboxInfo) error`\n65:   - `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID) error`\n66:   - File: `pkg/router/store.go` (or import from pkg/store)\n67:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestStoreInterface -v`\n68: \n69: - [ ] **T3.2**: Define `Logger` interface\n70:   - Methods: `Info(msg, keysAndValues...)`, `Error(msg, keysAndValues...)`, `Warning(msg, keysAndValues...)`\n71:   - File: `pkg/router/logger.go`\n72:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestLoggerInterface -v`\n73: \n74: ### Phase 4: JWTManager (ST-4)\n75: \n76: - [ ] **T4.1**: Define `JWTManager` interface\n77:   - `GenerateToken(ctx, kind, name, namespace) (string, error)`\n78:   - `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret(ctx) error`\n79:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n80:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTManagerInterface -v`\n81: \n82: - [ ] **T4.2**: Define `jwtManager` struct\n83:   - `privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey`\n84:   - `publicKey *rsa.PublicKey`\n85:   - `kubeClient kubernetes.Interface`\n86:   - `namespace string`\n87:   - `logger Logger`\n88:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n89:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTManagerStruct -v`\n90: \n91: - [ ] **T4.3**: Implement RSA key generation\n92:   - `rsa.GenerateKey(rand.Reader, 2048)`\n93:   - Private key: PKCS1 PEM encoding\n94:   - Public key: PKIX PEM encoding\n95:   - Helper functions: `encodePrivateKeyPEM`, `encodePublicKeyPEM`, `loadPrivateKeyPEM`\n96:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n97:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestRSAKeyGeneration -v`\n98: \n99: - [ ] **T4.4**: Implement `NewJWTManager(kubeClient, namespace, logger)` constructor\n100:   - Generate RSA 2048-bit key pair\n101:   - Initialize struct with all fields\n102:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n103:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestNewJWTManager -v`\n104: \n105: - [ ] **T4.5**: Implement `GenerateToken(ctx, kind, name, namespace)` method\n106:   - Create JWT with claims: `exp` (now+5m), `iat` (now), `iss=\"agentcube-router\"`\n107:   - Add custom claims: `kind`, `name`, `namespace`\n108:   - Sign with RS256 algorithm\n109:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n110:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTManager_GenerateToken -v`\n111: \n112: - [ ] **T4.6**: Implement `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret(ctx)` method\n113:   - Create K8s Secret with name `picod-router-identity`\n114:   - Handle `AlreadyExists` by loading existing secret\n115:   - Load keys from secret data\n116:   - Use `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` env var (default \"default\")\n117:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n118:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTManager_TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret -v`\n119: \n120: ### Phase 5: SessionManager (ST-5)\n121: \n122: - [ ] **T5.1**: Define `SessionManager` interface\n123:   - `GetSandboxBySession(ctx, sessionID, namespace, name, kind) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n124:   - File: `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n125:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestSessionManagerInterface -v`\n126: \n127: - [ ] **T5.2**: Define `manager` struct\n128:   - `storeClient Store`\n129:   - `workloadMgrAddr string`\n130:   - `httpClient *http.Client`\n131:   - `logger Logger`\n132:   - File: `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n133:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestManagerStruct -v`\n134: \n135: - [ ] **T5.3**: Implement `NewSessionManager(store, logger)` constructor\n136:   - Read `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` env var (required, fail if missing)\n137:   - Configure HTTP client: `Timeout=2m`, `MaxIdleConnsPerHost=100`\n138:   - Configure HTTP2: `ReadIdleTimeout=30s`, `PingTimeout=15s`\n139:   - File: `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n140:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestNewSessionManager -v`\n141: \n142: - [ ] **T5.4**: Implement `GetSandboxBySession(ctx, sessionID, namespace, name, kind)` method\n143:   - If `sessionID` empty: call `createSandbox(ctx, namespace, name, kind)`\n144:   - If `sessionID` present: call `storeClient.GetSession(ctx, sessionID)`\n145:   - Return `SandboxInfo` or error\n146:   - File: `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n147:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestSessionManager_GetSandboxBySession -v`\n148: \n149: - [ ] **T5.5**: Implement `createSandbox(ctx, namespace, name, kind)` internal method\n150:   - Build `CreateSandboxRequest` with Kind, Name, Namespace\n151:   - POST to `/v1/agent-runtime` for `AgentRuntimeKind`\n152:   - POST to `/v1/code-interpreter` for `CodeInterpreterKind`\n153:   - Add K8s SA token from `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` if available\n154:   - Parse `CreateSandboxResponse` and store via `CreateSession`\n155:   - Use namespace from `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` env var (default \"default\")\n156:   - File: `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n157:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestSessionManager_createSandbox -v`\n158: \n159: ### Phase 6: Middleware (ST-6)\n160: \n161: - [ ] **T6.1**: Implement `concurrencyLimitMiddleware(maxConcurrent)` function\n162:   - Use buffered channel as semaphore\n163:   - Capacity = `maxConcurrent` (default 1000 if <=0)\n164:   - `sem <- struct{}{}` to acquire slot\n165:   - `<-sem` to release slot (deferred)\n166:   - File: `pkg/router/middleware.go`\n167:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestConcurrencyLimitMiddleware -v`\n168: \n169: - [ ] **T6.2**: Implement 429 overload response\n170:   - `select` with `default` case when semaphore full\n171:   - Return HTTP 429 with `{\"error\": \"server overloaded\", \"code\": \"SERVER_OVERLOADED\"}`\n172:   - Call `c.Abort()` to stop processing\n173:   - File: `pkg/router/middleware.go`\n174:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestConcurrencyLimitMiddleware_Overload -v`\n175: \n176: - [ ] **T6.3**: Implement `loggingMiddleware` function\n177:   - Log request method, path, status, duration\n178:   - Use `logger.Info` with keys: method, path, status, duration\n179:   - File: `pkg/router/middleware.go`\n180:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestLoggingMiddleware -v`\n181: \n182: - [ ] **T6.4**: Implement `recoveryMiddleware` function\n183:   - Recover from panics\n184:   - Log error with stack trace\n185:   - Return HTTP 500 with `{\"error\": \"internal server error\"}`\n186:   - File: `pkg/router/middleware.go`\n187:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestRecoveryMiddleware -v`\n188: \n189: ### Phase 7: Reverse Proxy (ST-7)\n190: \n191: - [ ] **T7.1**: Implement `newReverseProxy(target, jwt, sessionID)` function\n192:   - Use `httputil.NewSingleHostReverseProxy(target)`\n193:   - Set custom `Director` function\n194:   - Set custom `ModifyResponse` function\n195:   - Set custom `ErrorHandler` function\n196:   - File: `pkg/router/reverse_proxy.go`\n197:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestReverseProxy -v`\n198: \n199: - [ ] **T7.2**: Implement `Director` function\n200:   - Path normalization: add leading `/` if missing\n201:   - Set `req.URL.Scheme`, `req.URL.Host`, `req.URL.Path`\n202:   - Set `req.Host` to target host\n203:   - Set forwarding headers: `X-Forwarded-Host`, `X-Forwarded-Proto`, `X-Forwarded-For`, `X-Real-IP`\n204:   - Inject JWT: `Authorization: Bearer <jwt>`\n205:   - File: `pkg/router/reverse_proxy.go`\n206:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestReverseProxy_Director -v`\n207: \n208: - [ ] **T7.3**: Implement `ModifyResponse` function\n209:   - Add `x-agentcube-session-id` header to response\n210:   - Value is the resolved session ID\n211:   - File: `pkg/router/reverse_proxy.go`\n212:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestReverseProxy_ModifyResponse -v`\n213: \n214: - [ ] **T7.4**: Implement `ErrorHandler` function\n215:   - Check for \"connection refused\" → HTTP 502 `sandbox unreachable`\n216:   - Check for \"timeout\" → HTTP 504 `sandbox timeout`\n217:   - Other errors → HTTP 500\n218:   - Return JSON response: `{\"error\": \"<message>\"}`\n219:   - File: `pkg/router/reverse_proxy.go`\n220:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestReverseProxy_ErrorHandler -v`\n221: \n222: - [ ] **T7.5**: Implement `selectEntryPoint(entryPoints, invocationPath)` helper\n223:   - Find matching entry point by path prefix\n224:   - Default to first entry point if no match\n225:   - Return nil if `entryPoints` is empty\n226:   - File: `pkg/router/reverse_proxy.go`\n227:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestSelectEntryPoint -v`\n228: \n229: - [ ] **T7.6**: Implement `buildTargetURL(entryPoint)` helper\n230:   - Parse `entryPoint.Endpoint` as URL\n231:   - Add protocol prefix if missing: `entryPoint.Protocol + \"://\" + endpoint`\n232:   - File: `pkg/router/reverse_proxy.go`\n233:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestBuildTargetURL -v`\n234: \n235: ### Phase 8: Handlers (ST-8)\n236: \n237: - [ ] **T8.1**: Implement `handleHealthLive(c)` handler\n238:   - Return HTTP 200\n239:   - Body: `{\"status\": \"alive\"}`\n240:   - File: `pkg/router/handlers.go`\n241:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestHandleHealthLive -v`\n242: \n243: - [ ] **T8.2**: Implement `handleHealthReady(c)` handler\n244:   - Check if `sessionManager != nil`\n245:   - If nil: HTTP 503, body: `{\"status\": \"not ready\", \"error\": \"session manager not available\"}`\n246:   - If valid: HTTP 200, body: `{\"status\": \"ready\"}`\n247:   - File: `pkg/router/handlers.go`\n248:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestHandleHealthReady -v`\n249: \n250: - [ ] **T8.3**: Implement `handleInvoke(c)` handler for invocation routing\n251:   - Extract `namespace`, `name`, `kind` from URL path params\n252:   - Extract `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n253:   - Call `sessionManager.GetSandboxBySession(ctx, sessionID, namespace, name, kind)`\n254:   - Update activity: `storeClient.UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID)` (1st)\n255:   - Select entry point from `SandboxInfo.EntryPoints`\n256:   - Generate JWT via `jwtManager.GenerateToken(ctx, kind, name, namespace)`\n257:   - Create reverse proxy and serve\n258:   - Update activity after proxy (2nd)\n259:   - Inject `x-agentcube-session-id` response header\n260:   - Handle errors with appropriate HTTP codes\n261:   - File: `pkg/router/handlers.go`\n262:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestHandleInvoke -v`\n263: \n264: - [ ] **T8.4**: Implement `handleAgentInvoke(c)` handler\n265:   - Set `kind = AgentRuntimeKind`\n266:   - Delegate to `handleInvoke`\n267:   - File: `pkg/router/handlers.go`\n268:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestHandleAgentInvoke -v`\n269: \n270: - [ ] **T8.5**: Implement `handleCodeInterpreterInvoke(c)` handler\n271:   - Set `kind = CodeInterpreterKind`\n272:   - Delegate to `handleInvoke`\n273:   - File: `pkg/router/handlers.go`\n274:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestHandleCodeInterpreterInvoke -v`\n275: \n276: - [ ] **T8.6**: Implement `handleGetSandboxError(c, err)` helper\n277:   - Check `apierrors.IsNotFound` → HTTP 404\n278:   - Check `apierrors.APIStatus` → use status code from APIStatus\n279:   - Other errors → HTTP 500 with `\"internal server error\"`\n280:   - File: `pkg/router/handlers.go`\n281:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestHandleGetSandboxError -v`\n282: \n283: ### Phase 9: Server (ST-9)\n284: \n285: - [ ] **T9.1**: Define `Server` struct\n286:   - `config *Config`\n287:   - `engine *gin.Engine`\n288:   - `httpServer *http.Server`\n289:   - `sessionManager SessionManager`\n290:   - `storeClient Store`\n291:   - `jwtManager JWTManager`\n292:   - `transport *http.Transport`\n293:   - `logger Logger`\n294:   - File: `pkg/router/server.go`\n295:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestServerStruct -v`\n296: \n297: - [ ] **T9.2**: Implement `NewServer(config, sessionManager, store, jwtManager, logger)` constructor\n298:   - Create `engine := gin.New()`\n299:   - Set Gin mode: `gin.ReleaseMode` if `!config.Debug`, `gin.DebugMode` if `config.Debug`\n300:   - Initialize shared `http.Transport`\n301:   - Configure `httpServer` with h2c, `ReadTimeout=30s`, `IdleTimeout=90s`\n302:   - Register routes with middleware\n303:   - File: `pkg/router/server.go`\n304:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestNewServer -v`\n305: \n306: - [ ] **T9.3**: Implement route registration\n307:   - `/health/live` → `handleHealthLive` (no middleware)\n308:   - `/health/ready` → `handleHealthReady` (no middleware)\n309:   - `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path` → `handleAgentInvoke` (GET, POST)\n310:   - `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path` → `handleCodeInterpreterInvoke` (GET, POST)\n311:   - Apply middleware: `concurrencyLimitMiddleware`, `loggingMiddleware`, `recoveryMiddleware`\n312:   - File: `pkg/router/server.go`\n313:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestServer_Routes -v`\n314: \n315: - [ ] **T9.4**: Implement `Start(ctx)` method without TLS\n316:   - Configure h2c server with `http2.Server`\n317:   - Call `httpServer.ListenAndServe()`\n318:   - Launch goroutine for graceful shutdown on context cancel\n319:   - File: `pkg/router/server.go`\n320:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestServer_Start -v`\n321: \n322: - [ ] **T9.5**: Implement `Start(ctx)` method with TLS\n323:   - If `config.EnableTLS == true`: call `httpServer.ListenAndServeTLS(config.TLSCert, config.TLSKey)`\n324:   - Return error if cert/key files missing\n325:   - File: `pkg/router/server.go`\n326:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestServer_StartTLS -v`\n327: \n328: - [ ] **T9.6**: Implement graceful shutdown\n329:   - On context cancel: call `httpServer.Shutdown(shutdownCtx)`\n330:   - Shutdown deadline: 10s\n331:   - Server stops accepting new connections\n332:   - Existing connections complete before shutdown\n333:   - File: `pkg/router/server.go`\n334:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestServer_GracefulShutdown -v`\n335: \n336: - [ ] **T9.7**: Implement `Stop()` method\n337:   - Call `httpServer.Shutdown(ctx)` directly\n338:   - Use 10s timeout context\n339:   - File: `pkg/router/server.go`\n340:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestServer_Stop -v`\n341: \n342: ### Phase 10: Integration Tests (ST-10)\n343: \n344: - [ ] **T10.1**: Implement `handleInvoke` integration test\n345:   - Test session resolution flow without session header → creates sandbox\n346:   - Test session resolution with valid session header → lookup from store\n347:   - Test session resolution with invalid session → 404 response\n348:   - File: `pkg/router/handlers_test.go`\n349:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestHandleInvoke_Integration -v`\n350: \n351: - [ ] **T10.2**: Implement proxy flow integration test\n352:   - Test successful proxy → response header with session ID\n353:   - 